==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dormer window
<hw>Dor"mer win"dow</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Literally, the window of a
sleeping apartment. F. <ets>dormir</ets> to sleep. See <er>Dormant</er>,
<pos>a.</pos> & <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A window
pierced in a roof, and so set as to be vertical while the roof slopes
away from it. Also, the gablet, or houselike structure, in which it is
contained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dormitive</ent>⟦br⟧
